OL,6,FOur investigation also discovered that
OL,7,Fthe Medicines Regulator (MHRA) had
OL,8,Fmisled the public for up to 25 years
OL,9,Fabout when the drug was withdrawn and
OL,10,Fissued an apology last month.
OL,12,FThe MHRA had falsely claimed that
OL,13,Fdoctors were advised to stop using the
OL,14,Fdrug for use in pre-menopausal women
OL,15,Fin 1973.
OL,17,FIn September 2025, it admitted that
OL,18,Finformation was incorrect, and the
OL,19,Fdrug was not stopped for use in
OL,20,Fpregnancy until the 1980s, more than a
OL,21,Fdecade after cancer risks were known.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G16/19
